#
# Accepted (unfixable-by-us) findings. Each entry is a CVE whose Trivy-listed
# "fixed" version is NOT actually shipped by the upstream repo, or is mis-matched
# to a non-vulnerable subpackage. Revisit when upstream rebuilds.

# CVE-2026-31789 — Trivy attributes an OpenSSL *library* CVE to the
# `openssl-config` subpackage (config FILES only — no vulnerable code), and the
# listed fix (3.6.2-r0) is not in the Wolfi repo (`apk upgrade` is a no-op; the
# repo's newest openssl-config is the installed 3.3.0-r5). Remove once Wolfi
# rebuilds openssl-config past the affected range.
CVE-2026-31789
